Computer science is a very modern and rapidly developing field of knowledge, used in almost all spheres of our lives. A graduate of computer science is a person who has knowledge and skills that are valued at home and abroad.

*Ideal candidate.

This is a direction for passionate people. Practice is much more important here than in other fields. Computer science, although based on strict knowledge, requires design ability and imagination. The ideal candidate should have an eagerness to learn and be in touch with news, because in computer science everything changes very quickly. The ability to think independently and aptitude in science subjects are useful.

*Why is it worth studying computer science at UMK?

UMK has very modern scientific and teaching facilities, which is especially important when studying computer science.

Excellent staff works here, guaranteeing that the student will learn the latest technologies and IT knowledge.

The Faculty of Mathematics and Computer Science provides comfortable conditions for studying and realizing one's own interests, for example, in scientific circles.

*What to do after graduation.

Graduates of UMK computer science can find employment in the operation of information systems of companies or in the creation and management of websites. The acquired skills allow them to take up positions:

* administrator of computer systems and networks in companies, enterprises;
* programmer of web and mobile applications;
* internet network programmer;
* designer and analyst of database systems;
* designer of decision-making systems;
* consultant for complex informatization of enterprises;
* implementer of information systems and coordinator of informatization projects;
* employees of laboratories and other research and computing centers.

More about part-time studies at the Faculty of Mathematics and Computer Science of the University of Krakow (link: https://www.mat.umk.pl/web/wmii/studia/studia-niestacjonarne)
